// `Delete` statement (§3.3). The parser is permissive on operand
// shape — lvalue/rvalue classification and the §9.2 trap diagnostics are
// sema's job.

// Lvalue operands: plain variable, field, indexed. (`field` is a CB
// keyword, hence the `.field1` spelling — matches the §3.3 spec example.)
Delete x
Delete y.field1
Delete arr[0]

// Rvalue operand: call expression. Sema will later flag the rvalue form
// per §3.3 ("any CB variable or field still holding the freed reference
// now dangles").
Delete First(MyType)

// `Delete` inside a single-line `If` — the canonical loop-cleanup pattern
// from §3.3's worked examples ("If n.dead Then Delete n").
If n.dead Then Delete n

// Recovery: missing operand on its own line — diagnostic, statement is
// `Stmt::Error` and the parser moves on.
Delete

// Recovery: missing operand before `:` separator. `Print` is not a keyword
// in this language, so the following `Print 1` parses as a paren-less call
// to a user-defined sub named `Print`.
Delete : Print 1
